Determining lies, or "recognizing lies", is a necessary skill that everyone should acquire, whether for personal or work reasons.
However, it is not a social game that would be similar, say, to Charade, when one shouts, "I have you." Deception is a serious branch of science working with scientific data collected over the past six decades at prestigious universities in the course of detailed research projects, in the field of psychology, and in the field of philosophy.
