A trained lie identifier can reveal the truth from a sentence structure, small facial expressions, the way questions are created and their timing.
I have spent several years gathering scientific knowledge from a vast and developing industry relating to lie detection, and it is clear that deception detection is a modern skill that can be easily learned and in today's complex world can be of great help to you - especially if you are in the middle of your work.
Good liars can read well in others, let them be watered in caution, direct their emotions, and intuitively realize how the other party accepts them.
