Notice the subject’s language as well.
Scott Peterson's famous story of how he once disavowed and used the past tense when he claimed that his murdered wife was alive, sparking a nationwide search for her body.
Deceptive individuals may also express themselves moderately: "I had no sexual relations with that lady... Miss Lewinska" or repeat the difficult question altogether.
The most common verbal signs are only very minor.
Someone can use a lot of "softening language" when answering a difficult question: "Well... to tell the truth... from what I know... to my best conscience."
